First, all large visible litter along the entire stretch was counted. Then two transects, one meter wide, were made from the middle waterline to the upper part of the shore. In the transects, everything small and things that were hidden in the seaweed wall were counted. The result from the transects was recalculated to 100 m. Total amount of litter was calculated by summing all the large visible with what was calculated in the transects.
